---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const pageTitle = "Research and Engagement";
const pageDescription = "My academic research on technology, learning, and everyday practice and how I tell people about it";
---

<BaseLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <main class="py-12">

    <h1 class="font-pixel text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-8 leading-relaxed hero-title">Research and Engagement</h1>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
      I research what happens when people encounter technology that wasn't designed for them. <br/>
      Then, I try to make sure what I find out helps those people!
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">My work spans:</p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-2">
      <li>Young people's use of emerging technologies</li>
      <li>Socio-technical cybersecurity</li>
      <li>Data protection and people's understanding of data use</li>
      <li>Digital safety and user agency</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Jump navigation -->
    <nav class="jump-nav flex flex-wrap gap-3 mb-8">
      <a href="#projects" class="jump-link">Research Projects</a>
      <a href="#publications" class="jump-link">Publications</a>
      <a href="#policy" class="jump-link">Policy</a>
      <a href="#talks" class="jump-link">Talks and Public Engagement</a>
      <a href="#consultancy" class="jump-link">Consultancy</a>
    </nav>

    <div class="pixel-divider-thin mb-8"></div>
    <section id="projects">
      <h2 class="pixel-header font-pixel text-lg sm:text-xl mb-6">Current Projects</h2>

      <div class="mb-6 space-y-6">
        <div class="pixel-card bg-muted p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">
            <a href="https://www.projectcaise.co.uk">Project CAISE</a> - Principal Investigator
          </h3>
          <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
            Project CAISE (Children and AI in School and Elsewhere) is a longitudinal study funded by the British Academy Postdoctoral Fellowship. Working collaboratively with young people, their schools, and families, the project uses sociomaterial methods to understand how children engage with generative AI across different contexts of their lives.
          </p>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            The project will produce academic publications, develop resources for educators and parents navigating AI with children, and contribute evidence-based recommendations for policy and practice around youth AI literacy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pixel-card bg-muted p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">
            <a href="https://chaild.org">CHAILD</a> - Associated Researcher
          </h3>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            CHAILD is a UKRI research project (jointly run by University of Oxford, UCL and Utrecht University) defining and designing children's agency in the age of AI.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    
      <h2 class="pixel-header font-pixel text-lg sm:text-xl mb-4">Fellowships and Affiliations</h2>

      <div class="mb-6 space-y-6">
        <div class="pixel-card bg-muted p-5">
          <p class="mb-2">
            <strong><a href="https://www.thebritishacademy.ac.uk/">British Academy</a> Postdoctoral Fellow</strong>, UCL Knowledge Lab (2025-2028)
          </p>
          <p class="opacity-75">
            Researching with young people to understand their evolving relationships with generative AI, using sociomaterial methods.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pixel-card bg-muted p-5">
          <p class="mb-2">
            <strong>Associate Fellow</strong>, <a href="https://www.riscs.org.uk/">Research Institute for Sociotechnical Cyber Security (RISCS)</a> (2026)
          </p>
          <p class="opacity-75">
            Contributing to understanding socio-technical dimensions of cybersecurity.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pixel-card bg-muted p-5">
          <p class="mb-2">
            <strong>Honorary Member</strong>, <a href="https://research.kent.ac.uk/cyber/">Institute of Cyber Security for Society (iCSS)</a> - University of Kent
          </p>
          <p class="opacity-75">
            
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pixel-divider-thin my-6"></div>

      <h2 class="pixel-header font-pixel text-lg sm:text-xl mb-4">Past Projects/Research Groups</h2>

      <ul class="compact-list mb-6 space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Project CHAI</strong> - Cyber Hygiene in AI-enabled domestic life. (EPRSC-funded, run by University of Greenwich, UCL Knowledge Lab, University of Reading, University of Bristol)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Digital Futures Commission</strong> - Data protection and cybersecurity practices in state schools in England. (Digital Futures Commission is part of 5Rights Foundation)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Ransomware Harms and the Victim Experience</strong> - Impacts of ransomware on victims, economies and societies. (RISCS and NCSC-funded, run by University of Kent and RUSI)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Ransomware: The Role of Cyber-Insurance</strong> - Understanding the relationship between cyber-insurance and ransomware attacks. (RISCS and NCSC-funded, run by University of Kent and RUSI)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Approaches to Support Families' Engagement with Cybersecurity for Home IoT Devices</strong> - Exploration of the ways in which parents/guardians and children understand, manage and discuss cybersecurity of smart devices. (NCSC-funded, PhD at University of Kent)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Data Portability in Consumer IoT</strong> - Investigation of the ability to exercise Article 20 GDPR for smart devices, and consumer desire to do so (MPA at UCL STEaPP)
        </li>
         <li>
          <strong>PETRAS - National Centre of Excellence for IoT Systems Cybersecurity</strong> - Various projects including: children's IoT privacy and security, IoT and the d/Deaf community
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <div class="pixel-divider-thin my-6"></div>

    <section id="publications">
      <h2 class="pixel-header font-pixel text-lg sm:text-xl mb-4">Publications</h2>

      <p class="leading-relaxed">
        View my publications on <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=LXDgjZcAAAAJ&hl=en">Google Scholar</a> or <a href="https://profiles.ucl.ac.uk/89907-sarah-turner/">UCL Profiles</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="pixel-divider-thin my-6"></div>

     <section id="policy">
      <h2 class="pixel-header font-pixel text-lg sm:text-xl mb-4">Policy</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed"> I aim to work on research projects that generate useful evidence for policy-making.
      </p><br/>
       <p class="mb-4">My previous projects have resulted in:</p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-2">
      <li>Published evidence in UK Select Committee reports</li>
      <li>Reports and white papers for policy-makers and civil service members</li>
      <li>Briefings for executive and legislative branches of international governments</li>
    </ul>
     </section>

<div class="pixel-divider-thin my-6"></div>

    <section id="talks">
      <h2 class="pixel-header font-pixel text-lg sm:text-xl mb-4">Talks and Public Engagement</h2>
<p class="leading-relaxed"> I love talking to people about how the findings of my research can help them have better relationships with digital technologies.
     </p><br/>
       <p class="mb-4">I have previously talked to...</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-2">
      <li>Industry conference participants about data portability</li>
      <li>Journalists on different aspects of my research</li>
      <li>University research groups on different aspects of my research</li>
      <li>University students about cyber crime, ethics and the law</li>
      <li>Secondary school students about personal data use and tracking</li>
      <li>Primary and secondary school students about personal threat modelling</li>
      <li>Primary school students about personal cyber security</li>
    </ul>

    </section>

    <div class="pixel-divider-thin my-6"></div>

    <section id="consultancy">
      <h2 class="pixel-header font-pixel text-lg sm:text-xl mb-4">Consultancy work</h2>
<p class="leading-relaxed"> I help local, national and multi-national organisations with specific questions relating to digital techology use. 
      </p><br/>
       <p class="mb-4">Some previous examples:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-2">
      <li>Refreshing organisational guidance around technology use</li>
      <li>Supporting curriculum development</li>
      <li>Building and reviewing training documentation</li>
      <li>Creating robust organisational risk and control environments</li>
 
    </ul>

    </section>
    <div class="pixel-divider-thin my-6"></div>

    <h2 class="pixel-header font-pixel text-lg sm:text-xl mb-4">Contact</h2>

    <p class="leading-relaxed">
      Want to have a chat about my research? Want me to give a talk or do some consultancy work? <br/><a href="/contact">Get in touch</a>.
    </p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero-title {
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--pixel-cyan), var(--pixel-magenta), var(--pixel-blue));
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  }
  .pixel-card {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--pixel-cyan);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
  }
  .pixel-card:hover {
    border-left-color: var(--pixel-magenta);
    box-shadow: 0 0 12px var(--pixel-glow);
  }
  a {
    color: var(--pixel-text);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--pixel-cyan);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.15s ease;
  }
  a:hover {
    background: var(--pixel-cyan);
    color: var(--bg-main);
  }
  .jump-nav {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .jump-link {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--pixel-cyan);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--pixel-cyan);
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: all 0.15s ease;
  }
  .jump-link:hover {
    background: var(--pixel-cyan);
    color: var(--bg-main);
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--pixel-glow);
  }
  .compact-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 0;
  }
  .compact-list li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--main-border-color);
  }
  .compact-list li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
</style>